Website Smoke Test Checklist

Purpose

A smoke test is a quick, high-level verification that the most critical functionality of a website is working after a deployment, update, or configuration change.

Estimated Time: 5–15 minutes

⸻

Environment

Website:

Version/Release:

Date Tested:

Tester:

Browser(s):

Device:

⸻

Homepage

* Homepage loads successfully
* No obvious visual layout issues
* Logo displays correctly
* Navigation menu functions
* Footer displays correctly
* No broken images
* No obvious spelling or grammar errors

⸻

Navigation

* Primary navigation links work
* Footer links work
* Internal links open correctly
* External links open correctly
* No 404 pages encountered

⸻

Authentication (If Applicable)

* Login page loads
* Valid user can log in
* Invalid credentials show an error
* User can log out
* Protected pages require authentication

⸻

Forms

For each major form:

* Form loads
* Required fields are enforced
* Successful submission works
* Error messages display correctly
* Confirmation message appears

⸻

Content

* Major pages load successfully
* Images display correctly
* Videos or embedded media work
* Downloads function properly

⸻

Mobile Responsiveness

* Navigation works
* Text is readable
* Buttons are usable
* Images resize correctly
* No overlapping content

⸻

Browser Compatibility

Tested Browsers:

* Chrome
* Edge
* Firefox
* Safari

⸻

Performance

* Pages load within an acceptable time
* No obvious delays
* No loading errors

⸻

Security

* HTTPS is enabled
* No browser security warnings
* Sensitive pages require authentication

⸻

Console Check

* No JavaScript errors
* No obvious network failures

⸻

Result

Smoke Test Status

* PASS
* FAIL

⸻

Notes

Document any issues, observations, or recommendations discovered during testing.